WEBVTT

NOTE
HealthPulse Edge — demo subtitle template.
Contest allows up to 3:00; the cuts below sketch a 90-second floor.
Expand each scene to 30-40 sec for a 2:30 target. Adjust timestamps to final cut.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
A 25-bed hospital on tribal land in northern Arizona.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:11.000
Same federal CMS reporting obligations as Mayo Clinic.
No IT department. No analytics team.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:16.000
This Mac Mini runs Gemma 4 entirely on-device.
Watch the airplane-mode indicator.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Marlene types: "find the top 3 care gaps and tell me which one to tackle first."

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Three function calls. Care gap finder. Facility benchmark. Cross-cutting analysis.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Sepsis bundle compliance is 64 percent — fourteen points below peer median.
Refresh the 3-hour bundle education and audit antibiotic timing.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.000
Stanford-grade quality analytics. Four seconds. On a four hundred dollar box.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:54.000
Now Marlene holds a handwritten patient experience survey to the webcam.

00:00:54.000 --> 01:01:02.000
Gemma 4 vision transcribes it. Adds it to local FHIR. Compliance ledger logs the action: PHI egress, false.

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:10.000
Submit to CMS. Sovereignty Mode requires a tribal council co-signature key.

01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:18.000
Redaction sub-agent strips a hundred forty-two PHI fields.
Differential privacy noise applied. Envelope signed.

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:25.000
Frontier intelligence does not require a frontier datacenter.

01:01:25.000 --> 01:01:30.000
HealthPulse Edge. Built on Gemma 4. github dot com slash sgharlow slash gemma-health.
